<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920312-0144</DOCNO><DOCID>920312-0144.</DOCID><HL>   Secom Authorizes Option</HL><DATE>03/12/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15</SO><CO>   SECM</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)</IN><NS>PRIVATE PLACEMENTS (PVT)</NS><RE>MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NOVI, Mich. -- Secom General Corp. said its boardauthorized the issuance of a 30-day option to businessmanWarren Avis for the purchase of one million shares of Secomcommon stock at $7.50 a share.   The option expires April 9, the company said. Commonshares issued from the option will be &quot;restricted shares&quot;pursuant to SEC Rule 144. Secom said the exercise of theoption is subject to the execution of a definitive agreement.</LP><TEXT>   &quot;We believe that additional equity of this magnitude willallow Secom to take advantage of opportunities in basicmanufacturing that will enhance shareholder value,&quot; saidDavid J. Marczak, Secom's secretary and treasurer.</TEXT></DOC>